    "details": {
      "en": {
        "id": "en",
        "purpose": "To diagnose autoimmune hepatitis.",
        "keywords": [
          "autoimmune",
          "hepatitis",
          "biopsy",
          "AIH"
        ],
        "use": "Use in patients with established hepatitis and available liver biopsy results, but unclear diagnosis.\nFormula:\nAddition of the selected points:\nVariable\t                                            Points\nSex\t  \n Male\t0\nFemale\t2\n\n\nALP:AST or ALP:ALT ratio\t\n<1.5\t        2\n1.5-3.0\t0\n>3.0\t        -2\n\n\nSerum globulins or IgG,                                                         >2.0                 3\ntimes above upper limit of normal\t                                      1.5-2.0              2\n\t                                                                                      1.0-1.5              1\n\t                                                                                      <1.0                  0\n\nAntinuclear antibody (ANA), smooth muscle antibody (SMA), \nor liver/kidney microsomal type 1 (LKM-1) antibody\n>1:80\t3\n1:80\t        2\n1:40\t        1\n<1:40\t0\n\nAnti-mitochondrial antibody (AMA)\nPositive\t-4\nNegative\t0\n\nHepatitis viral markers\nPositive\t-3\nNegative\t+3\n\nRecent or current use of hepatotoxic drugs\nYes\t-4\nNo\t1\n\nAverage alcohol intake\n<25 g/day\t2\n25-60 g/day\t0\n>60 g/day\t-2\n\nLiver histology: \nInterface hepatitis\t3\nPredominantly lymphoplasmacytic infiltrate\t1\nRosetting of liver cells\t1\nNo interface hepatitis, not predominantly lymphoplasmacytic infiltrate, and no rosetting of liver cells\t-5\nBiliary changes (bile duct changes typical of primary biliary cirrhosis or primary scleroisng cholangitis, and/or periportal ductal reaction with copper-associated protein accumulation)\t-3\nOther changes (any other prominent features suggesting different etiology)\t-3\n\nOther autoimmune disease(s) (in patient or 1st degree relatives): \nNo\t0\nYes\t2\n\nOptional additional parameters\nSeropositivity for other defined autoantibodies4\t2\nHLA-DR3 or HLA-DR4\t1\n\nResponse to therapy:\nComplete\t2\nRelapse\t3\n\nInterpretation:\nAIH Score\tPre- or post treatment\tDiagnosis\n>15\t                          Pre-treatment\tDefinite AIH\n10-15\t\t                                        Probable AIH\n>17\t                          Post-treatment\tDefinite AIH\n12-17\t\t                                        Probable AIH\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\t                                                                                       ",
        "copyright": "Cambio CDS"
      }
    },
    "other_details": {
      "references": "1. Alvarez F, Berg PA, Bianchi FB, Bianchi L, Burroughs AK, Cancado EL, Chapman RW, Cooksley WG, Czaja AJ, Desmet VJ, Donaldson PT, Eddleston AL, Fainboim L, Heathcote J, Homberg JC, Hoofnagle JH, Kakumu S, Krawitt EL, Mackay IR, MacSween RN, Maddrey WC, Manns MP, McFarlane IG, Meyer zum BÃ¼schenfelde KH, Zeniya M, et al. International Autoimmune Hepatitis Group Report: review of criteria for diagnosis of autoimmune hepatitis. J Hepatol. 1999 Nov;31(5):929-38. doi: 10.1016/s0168-8278(99)80297-9. PMID: 10580593.\n2. Czaja AJ. Performance parameters of the diagnostic scoring systems for autoimmune hepatitis. Hepatology. 2008 Nov;48(5):1540-8. doi: 10.1002/hep.22513. PMID: 18924244."
    }
